Goal:
Find the maximum length substring where we can replace at most k characters
to make all characters the same.

Key Formula:
window_size - maxFreq <= k

Brute Force Approach:
- Fix starting index i
- Expand ending index j
- Use a map to store character frequencies
- Track maxFreq (most frequent char in current window)
- If valid (window_size - maxFreq <= k), update result

Key Insight:
Only the most frequent character matters.
All other characters must be <= k to replace.
